            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This is cool.\r\n\r\nThe one annoying thing is that the `vim.opt` is not really the long-term interface we want, so we really need either:\r\n\r\n- `vim.make_option_mt()` returns something that looks more like https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/20107#issuecomment-1240069511\r\n- or, just make `vim.g` [more ergonomic](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/12544#issuecomment-1116794687) without trying to fit the \"options\" interface into it",
