            "body": "> doesnt rely on requiring lua modules\r\n\r\nyes, but that should be achievable by https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/12544#issuecomment-1116794687\r\n\r\n> has builtin typechecking (plugin author doesnt need to validate options themselves through a `.setup()` interface)\r\n\r\nit's not really builtin because the `info` structure in your code sample is basically doing what `vim.validate()` does, in about the same amount of code.\r\n\r\nAlso don't think we want to encourage \"flags\"-style options, or the other quirks of legacy vim options, but I guess `vim.make_option_mt` would allow that?",
